; Condition gate flip-flop under @differential retraction: retracting the
; last supporting row of condition `c` closes the gate mid-flow, so every
; downstream derivation through the positive test must retract and the
; negative test must re-derive; re-adding support reopens the gate and the
; positive derivations must come back. Several flip cycles run, with item
; data arriving both while the gate is open and while it is closed, plus a
; partial support retraction (two supporting rows, drop one: `c` must stay
; true) and a same-batch swap (retract one supporting row and add another in
; a single differential message: `c` must never observably flip).
;
; `item` is @differential too, so item rows are retracted while the gate is
; open (gated row must retract with it) and while it is closed (ungated row
; must retract), and a retracted item must not resurrect through later gate
; flips.

#message support(i32 S) @differential.
#message item(i32 X) @differential.

#local backing(i32 S).
#local stored(i32 X).

#query gated(free i32 X).
#query ungated(free i32 X).

backing(S) : support(S).
stored(X) : item(X).

c : backing(_).

gated(X) : stored(X), c.
ungated(X) : stored(X), !c.
